# Test 2 — Tracked Output

Tracked output for the surveillance footage sequence (529 frames @ 30 fps, 3840×2160).

The oblique camera angle exposes the car's side panels, windows, and wheel arches, yielding
137 stable corners held throughout all 529 frames. Velocity prediction keeps the bounding
box tracking cleanly through the exit phase with no tracker dropout.

